Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,taking me through all those levels again\Nyou know and uh in doing it we presented
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the dualities that hold each level of\Nconsciousness where it is. Every level
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:19:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects\Nan aversion and an attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.32,0:19:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the duality of the aversion, the\Nattraction is a is a perceptual
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.28,0:19:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion. And when you see through it\Nand drop it, you instantly move to a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.44,0:19:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,different level of consciousness.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we did um the dualities\Nuh for the lower levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.79,0:19:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from from uh we finished them. Where's\Nour thing that we always forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've forgotten this all over the place.\NBob Henderson must have spent half an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.36,0:19:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,evening packaging it all up and\Ncarefully mailing it to me after I spoke
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.96,0:19:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at Prescott.\NAnyway, so what we did in the first part
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.12,0:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the book is the dualities. So we\Nstarted at the bottom and we moved up
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought at each each lecture I'll\Npresent you know one slide. So we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.84,0:19:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,slide of the dualities that characterize\Neach level of consciousness. So today
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll start at the bottom and then each\Nlecture will move on up. See? So each
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one now the these this these levels\Naren't where we live. Um nobody how many
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,people in this audience don't live there\Nbut they are momentary they are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.28,0:20:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,transitory\Nuh your consciousness level can be you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,know here and suddenly you go into guilt\Nshame grief fear desire so these are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.88,0:20:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,eancent\Nup uh
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so one's consciousness level is that\Nwhich is dominant it's dominant but it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.76,0:20:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't exclude uh these things coming\Nup why do they come up they come up from
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.08,0:20:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconscious\NThey come up from the individual
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious unconscious.\NUh some of them are things that were
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.72,0:20:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,projected into the world and now that\Nyou're taking spiritual responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.24,0:20:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly feel guilt about them. And\Nso, but that's transitory. That's not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.79,0:20:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,where you are.\NHowever, we should know about them. And
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh so we're going to uh cover cover all\Nthe levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so how many people here are new\Ntoday?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.36,0:21:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right. All right. So the the\Nthe the contextualization of the lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.52,0:21:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nto to cover the basics and add something
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.76,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,new. We cover the basics for those who\Nare new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't spend a long time on them, but\Nwe do cover them and then we add
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.91,0:21:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,something new for the people who have\Nbeen here many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.28,0:21:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we always have a a review of the old\Nand an introduction of the new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.76,0:21:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When there isn't any more new, the\Nlectures stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.67,0:21:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be new. There's nothing more\Nto say other than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:22:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, folks, you're on your own. Yeah.\NAll right. So what we're really doing is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.48,0:22:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting spiritual truth in a\Ndifferent context than classic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.24,0:22:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,classically presented via religion and\Nvarious spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.76,0:22:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh groups and organizations which become\Nformalized into sort of ecclesiastic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.28,0:22:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,dogma\Ncomplete with with misunderstandings of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.67,0:22:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth that was originally spoken.\NBut some centuries later
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.08,0:22:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,um it's misinterpreted and those errors\Nstand out glaringly glaringly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.76,0:22:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So phen all phenomenon are\Nhappening of their own spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.00,0:22:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that they're being caused by\Nsomething
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is a error of perception.\NThe mind tries to explain phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.60,0:23:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, frankly, the mind is too dumb to\Nexplain phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.24,0:23:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even know why a rabbit is a\Nrabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.79,0:23:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It can explain genetics. It can give\Nyou. Those are all things about, but
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.28,0:23:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they have nothing to do with what it is\Nto be a rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.72,0:23:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask any rabbit.\NI say, "Rabbit, what is it like to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.32,0:23:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,rabbit?" He said, "I don't know. What\Ndoes rabbit mean?" Said, "You don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.84,0:23:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what a rabbit is?" No. I get the\Nencyclopedia. Susie, you get me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.32,0:23:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,encyclopedia.\NRabbit. Sit down. Rabbit. Okay. I read
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.00,0:23:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the rabbit. The whole thing. Takes me\Nabout 15 minutes to read all through
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.36,0:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,rabbit. I says, "Now,\Nwhat do you think of that? What? That's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.55,0:23:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what you are." He says, "That's not what\NI am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:24:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Well, then what are you?" He\Nsaid, "I'm me."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.72,0:24:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're the same as the rabbit. The\Nrabbit, all he knows is that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.24,0:24:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he's who he is, what he is. That's all\Nwe really know. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.36,0:24:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all the rest is elaborate. You don't\Nneed any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.00,0:24:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're out at sea\Nand a little boat and the wind is coming
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.72,0:24:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,up, what the encyclopedia says about\Nhumanity is pretty relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.32,0:24:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very intensely just being who you\Nare
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.24,0:24:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and asking God's intervention in the\Nmatter, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.03,0:24:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So intention then is very\Npowerful because the will is powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.96,0:24:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the will that sets karmic destiny\Nvery powerful. So to surrender to God to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.67,0:25:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,say\Nto commit to commit to to the Lord to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.67,0:25:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,God to divinity to enlightenment\Nwhatever you want to call it now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.24,0:25:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,completely changes your future\Naltogether
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.32,0:25:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,completely changes it not by virtue of\Ncausality but by virtue of intention
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.40,0:25:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which changes the field.\NEverything comes about as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.36,0:25:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field\Nand not of the linear ego. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.52,0:25:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As the consequence then by commitment\Nyou have now become
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.88,0:25:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,something different that what you than\Nwhat you were before you made the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.32,0:25:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment.\NIt's like a change in the barometric
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.44,0:25:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pressure. Now all of the weather is\Ngoing to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.40,0:25:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,not caused by anything but as a\Nconsequence of the barometric pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.27,0:25:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the barometric pressure itself\Ndoesn't really cause anything. It's the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.79,0:26:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,local condition.\NSo what you see then is potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming actuality\Nunder the circumstances that prevail at
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.88,0:26:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the time. The seed doesn't emerge until\Nthe sunlight, the warmth, and the water
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.03,0:26:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are appropriate,\Nbut they don't cause the seed to grow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.48,0:26:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,into a flower.\NThe other thing you'll notice if you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.44,0:26:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,skip\Nediting the world mentally
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.40,0:26:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is that things do not go from uncomplete\Nto complete. They do not go from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.72,0:26:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,imperfect to perfect.\NThey go from perfect to perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.91,0:26:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All things at all moments are perfect.\NImperfection is a rejection of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.76,0:26:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mentalization. Yeah. So\Neverything by virtue of being what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.84,0:27:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is already perfection because all of\Ncreation is perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.12,0:27:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is the unmanifest becoming\Nmanifest. within the experiential domain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.36,0:27:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as creation. Creation unfolds\Nspontaneously as the consequence that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.64,0:27:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the source is innate to that which has\Nbeen created. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.08,0:27:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of thinking of change and\Ncausality, then what you're witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.08,0:27:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is really emergence.\Nemergence of potentiality becoming an
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality\Nat each moment of emergence. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.76,0:27:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect. This is perfectly the fist.\NThis is perfectly the part of the open
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.32,0:27:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,hand. This is this is perfectly this is\Nperfectly perfectly perfectly. So as the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.91,0:27:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,flower unfolds, you see first it's a\Nperfect bud. Then it's a perfect half
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.27,0:28:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,open rose. Then it's a perfect fully\Nthen it's a perfectly faded rose. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.67,0:28:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes perfect fertilizer.\NIt's perfect at every moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.67,0:28:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So things don't move from incomplete to\Ncomplete or from imperfection to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.24,0:28:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection. They move from complete to\Ncomplete and from perfect to perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.72,0:28:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The halfopen rose is completely a\Nhalfopen rose. It's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.20,0:28:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect.\NYou witness that spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.27,0:28:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection\Nprevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.64,0:28:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All things are manifesting their\Npotentiality. They're only being what
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.60,0:29:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they they are\Nand they can't be anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To be perfectly stupid is to be\Nperfectly stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.72,0:29:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you're supposed to be right\Nnow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.52,0:29:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Noodle himers, we call them.\NWhy? Because we were all once children
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.15,0:29:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and because the evolution of\Nconsciousness, we have uh by grace,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.39,0:29:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,divine grace, by karmic merit,\Nearned the right to be born a human. Not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.24,0:29:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,only to have been born a human, but to\Nhave heard of enlightenment. Rare still
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.88,0:29:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is it to have heard of enlightenment.\NRare it is to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.36,0:29:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A great karmic gift.\NRar yet is it to have heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.24,0:30:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment.\NRarest of all is it to have heard of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.32,0:30:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment and made the decision to\Nseek it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.03,0:30:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nby the words of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.44,0:30:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this is indeed a gifted audience\Nand I do bow to this audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.96,0:30:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All gifted here.\NAll here are gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.88,0:30:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Gifted as a consequence of intention.\NSomewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.60,0:30:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in history, this lifetime or sometime\Nthere was made that commitment by a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.20,0:30:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer, by a declaration, by a devotion,\Nby an inner decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.00,0:30:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That intention carries through forever.\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.12,0:31:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,let me think it over again.\NI meant I was going to be good for a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.96,0:31:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,while.\NI didn't mean to be good all weekend,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.67,0:31:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\Nis Saturday night included and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.32,0:31:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give the it a break. Saturday night\Noff
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.36,0:31:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it night indulgence. Big up be an\Nanimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.55,0:31:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunday morning you go to church. That's\Nthe whole idea, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.08,0:31:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what I did last night.\NAll right. So, that's all you really
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.79,0:31:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,need to know. Need to know and we could\Nleave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.03,0:32:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letting things go and seeing that\Neverything is manifesting as the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.84,0:32:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of a field.\NSo the universe is an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.44,0:32:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite fields of diminishing power and\Nas a consequence of that which things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.96,0:32:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,have become like an earn filing in a\Nmagnetic field each thing aligns itself
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.79,0:32:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where it needs to be. It then emerges,\Nits potentiality then emerges as an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.44,0:32:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality if conditions are appropriate.\NThere's no necessity to even conjure up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.96,0:32:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an intellectual\Nmax axiom such as causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.20,0:32:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality as an explanation calibrates\Nat 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.51,0:32:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth, you know, really starts\Naround 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.00,0:32:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore you have why science and\Nspirituality what's the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.24,0:33:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with them.\NAll right. So we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.00,0:33:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,recapitulate. We'll start with slide one\Nand then we're going to move through
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.39,0:33:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,rapidly.\NUh move through rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.36,0:33:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Move through rapidly. Yes. We're going\Nto move through rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.15,0:33:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, um, we now have a total of 60\Nslides to look from. And we, uh, we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.96,0:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thought eventually we'll put out a book\Nof slides and charts, you know, slides
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.72,0:33:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and charts. A lot of people have asked\Nfor them, just slides and charts. You
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.76,0:33:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have to read all that stuff cuz you just\Nget it in a hurry. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.84,0:33:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, this of course is very\Nwell known. We've explained it many
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.12,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,times. uh these have to do with the\Nevolution of consciousness. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithmic number. Therefore, as\Nconsciousness advances, it advances more
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.27,0:33:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and more rapidly. So, in the beginning,\Nit's slow. But as you move along, uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.51,0:34:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can be surprised by very sudden jumps in\Nconsciousness. Because of that, I tell
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.32,0:34:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,people what they need to know way along\Nthe pathway early.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.63,0:34:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't talk about the void today, but\Nthat's another thing we have to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.52,0:34:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about. And uh and the the the uh\Ntemptations that come along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.11,0:34:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where people fall off the pedestal.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.44,0:34:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh because each spiritual student in a\Nway is tested too, you know. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.32,0:34:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like there's something evil out there\Ntesting you. It's just that quality of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.20,0:34:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconscious.\NIt's that claw of the ego which seeks to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.39,0:34:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,persist.\NAnd when you say, "I'm going to be kind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.44,0:34:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of benevolent to everybody." Instantly a\Ndog bites your ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.48,0:34:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego says,\NI win.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.56,0:34:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Not going to get away from my clutches.\NWhose clutches are you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.59,0:35:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the clutches of the primitive\Nnarcissistic ego. The world would like
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.16,0:35:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to label it evil, bad, the devil, Satan,\Ngive it all kinds of personifications
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.07,0:35:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and then live in fear of their own\Npersonifications.
